ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCEFTA Rules of Origin Regulations
PrecisCanada-European Free Trade Association Free Trade Agreement (CEFTA) Rules of Origin Regulations implement, in Canada, the rules of origin negotiated by Canada and EFTA, which will be used to determine when goods have undergone sufficient production to qualify for preferential tariff treatment under the CEFTA. Preferential tariff treatment under the CEFTA, which reflects the actual reduction in specific rates of duty, has been implemented in the Customs Tariff through Bill C-2.
